draft [drɑːft] n 1. a plan, sketch, or drawing of something

DSL

this is the rough dsl I'm aiming for

//some test file
//make a mill
draft = require('draft');

//factory call to generate model - Post
post = draft.Post() //returns a vanilla, milled object
comment =  draft.Comment() //returns a saved milled model
comment = draft.Comment()({create: false}) //returns an unsaved milled model


//-----------

//how to create vanilla mill
draft.factory 'Post'
	username: Faker.Name.findName();
	email: etc.
	text: etc.

//how to create a Mongoose mill
draft.factory 'Comment'
	orm: Mongoose
	username: Faker.Name.findName();
	email: etc.
	text: etc.
